`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
**Architecture**: `useSwatches` uses `useSyncExternalStore` — a module-level store pattern where all `ColorPickerEnhanced` instances across the app share the same swatch list without needing React context. When one picker adds a swatch, every other mounted picker sees it instantly.

**UX detail**: Semi-transparent saved swatches render a checkerboard pattern underneath using the same `CHECKER` constant the opacity slider uses. This gives a visual cue that the swatch has < 100% opacity, matching how Webflow shows transparency.

**Removal via right-click**: Following the Webflow convention where context-menu on a swatch gives a "remove" action. Here it's direct (right-click removes immediately) since there's only one action.
